Updated tests and examples.

Improve QMetaType handing in QHttpServerRouter

The QMetaType converter registry is shared by all parts of Qt that uses
it. Check that a converter is already registered before trying to
register it. If registering fails, check that it has been registered by
another thread or give up.

Reviewed-by: Qt Submodule Update Bot <qt_submodule_update_bot@qt-project.org>

QHttpServerRouterRule: Ensure responder is moved out of

Ensure that the responder is moved out of when route is handled.
Websocket handling code assumes that this is the case. Failing to
do so results in two handlers connected to the socket's readyRead()
signal.

Fixes: QTBUG-120746

IOChunkedTransfer: Check that `sink` and `source` are not null before using them

Those QPointers are pointing to devices that can be destroyed early,
for example if a connection was closed before the transfer has completed.

This fixes a potential crash.

Fixes: QTBUG-121219
